id: pm-2xwh
title: "Search: persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting as default for pm search --semantic-weight"
description: "The per-query --semantic-weight override (pm-cy8i, closed) was shipped. However, there is no persistent search.tuning.hybrid_semantic_weight setting that applies as the project default without specifying it on every query. Agents and users who want a consistent hybrid bias must pass --semantic-weight on every invocation or configure it through an extension."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:search",config,hybrid,relevance
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:24.769Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-14T16:25:22.329Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Add `search.tuning.hybrid_semantic_weight: number (0..1)` to PmSettings\n- Add to settings-validator; config nested-settings alias (search_hybrid_semantic_weight)\n- pm search uses the settings value as default when --semantic-weight is not passed\n- Contract test / MCP contract table updated\n- pm config set search_hybrid_semantic_weight 0.7 works end-to-end"
parent: pm-ydp6
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Verified already-implemented persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting works end-to-end
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-14T16:23:39.448Z",maintainer-agent,"Verified already-implemented (resolver resolveHybridSemanticWeight reads search.hybrid_semantic_weight, settings-validator supports it, nested-settings descriptor search_hybrid_semantic_weight + ratio kind, runSearch uses it as --semantic-weight default). Confirmed end-to-end in sandbox: config set search_hybrid_semantic_weight 0.85 persists + applies. Never documented in CHANGELOG (only per-query pm-cy8i was) -> closing here surfaces the persistent setting. No new code needed."
close_reason: Verified already-implemented persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting works end-to-end
body: "## Context\n\nSession memory 2026-05-26 notes search.tuning reminders_weight and events_weight contract drift (pm-75du, closed). The `--semantic-weight` flag per-query was shipped as pm-cy8i.\n\nHowever, `src/core/shared/constants.ts` shows hybrid weight defaults but no `search.tuning.hybrid_semantic_weight` persistent settings key. An agent working primarily on code review might want to persist `semantic_weight: 0.8` to always favour semantic retrieval without specifying it each time.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `search.tuning.hybrid_semantic_weight: number (0..1)` to PmSettings\n- [ ] Add to settings-validator; config nested-settings alias (search_hybrid_semantic_weight)\n- [ ] pm search uses the settings value as default when --semantic-weight is not passed\n- [ ] Contract test / MCP contract table updated\n- [ ] pm config set search_hybrid_semantic_weight 0.7 works end-to-end\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/core/shared/constants.ts` — hybrid weight defaults exist but not as a user-configurable settings key\n- pm-cy8i (closed) — per-query override shipped but no persistent setting\n- `src/types.ts` SearchSettings — check for hybrid_semantic_weight field absence"
